RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RISKY SPIRIT was hustled along to dispute the pace outside RUNNING WATER, under steady urging in the lane and drew off inside the final eighth. RUNNING WATER was sent to contest the pace from inside, did not have enough left the last furlong but proved easily second best. TIGGER ATTACK chased from outside, was two wide on the bend, angled to the outside upper stretch and moved clear for third in the waning yards. BELLA FRANCESCA made a slight leap as she bore inward at the start, bumped solidly with RARE BEAUTY, saved ground, vied for third briefly for third deep stretch but could not sustain her bid late. JILL ATTACK stumbled a few strides from the gate, chased the top pair briefly while in path three through the turn then gave way for the stretch run. RARE BEAUTY unruly in the gate, was forced in once the race began, checked behind traffic and always outrun.

ENTRY.NAME: Running Water
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, easily 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Rare Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: unruly gate, forced in start, checked, outrun

ENTRY.NAME: Bella Francesca
ENTRY.COMMENT: bore in start, bumped, saved ground

ENTRY.NAME: Jill Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: stumbled after start, 3-path turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Risky Spirit
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 2-3 path turn, driven clear last 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Tigger Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2 wide turn, angled out upper stretch, got 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LITTLE MIGHTY MAN rated off the early speed, picked up his pace just off the inside on the bend, fanned to path three for the stretch run, was all out the last furlong, crowded as he took the advantage seventy yards out and moved clear in the waning yards. JACK VAN BERG shared the lead outside WINGING WAYS, moved clear and stayed just off the rail on the turn, began to wear down inside the final eighth, drifted out to brush with LITTLE MIGHTY MAN seventy yards out and continued to gradually yield. TIME HEIST angled out on the turn, lost ground fanning to path five entering the lane, rallied belatedly but was easily best of the others. KARAYEL chased from between horses, came into the stretch from path four and only make up minor ground late. PERFECT WAGER chased running widest through and also made up minor ground the final furlong. WINGING WAYS displayed early speed from inside but began to fade after three furlongs.

ENTRY.NAME: Time Heist
ENTRY.COMMENT: angled out turn, 5 wide stretch bid, closing

ENTRY.NAME: Little Mighty Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path turn, all out last 1/8, brushed late, moved clear

ENTRY.NAME: Karayel
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4 path turn, mild gain late

ENTRY.NAME: Winging Ways
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, thru early

ENTRY.NAME: Perfect Wager
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside trip, mild gain late

ENTRY.NAME: Jack Van Berg
ENTRY.OWNER: Cox John E Follmer John E and Colvis Gabriela V
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-path turn, weakened late, drifted out, brushed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 42. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DELTA LADY vied for the early lead outside UNEEKY, took a slight advantage into the bend, moved clear upper stretch, gradually drifted out as she began to wear down the final furlong but kept ROARINGLIKETHUNDER at bay. ROARINGLIKETHUNDER moved out widest midway on the backstretch, went for the lead outside DELTA LADY into the turn, did not stay with that one upper stretch, gradually angled out as DELTA LADY came out the last eighth, steadily closed the gap but came up short. BULU prominent between rivals early, angled out four wide on the bend and found best stride too late deep stretch. UNEEKY was sent to dispute the pace inside rivals but began to slowly yield after three furlongs. HUQOOQ chased from off the inside and was never a factor. WHITE CASHEL a step slow at the break, failed to menace in a ground-saving trip.

ENTRY.NAME: Huqooq
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-4 path, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: White Cashel
ENTRY.OWNER: Yates Lanny D and Thurman Austin
ENTRY.COMMENT: a step slow start, saved ground, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Bulu
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed between, 4 wide turn, late gain

ENTRY.NAME: Roaringlikethunder
ENTRY.COMMENT: bid 3 wide turn, gradually altered out last 1/8, came again

ENTRY.NAME: Uneeky
ENTRY.COMMENT: used early inside

ENTRY.NAME: Delta Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied between, 2 wide turn, gradually drifted out last 1/8, held

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 75. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Clai ming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MODAZZLE was sent to get the inside and share the lead with LORD SHAFTESBURY, moved clear on the bend, floated out some entering the lane, widened command under urging and was kept to task to the final seventy yards. I'M YOUR VALENTINE closed the gap three wide on the turn, moved clear for second upper stretch then could only maintain control of the place in the late going. PLAIN OR PEANUT was away slowly, gradually progressed from outside, lost ground four wide through the turn, made up ground on the top pair the last eighth and proved easily best of the others. MARY'S BOY, whose jockey did not carry a riding crop, was without much early speed, though urged along, saved ground and failed to menace. LORD SHAFTESBURY displayed early speed from outside but began to fade two wide on the bend.

ENTRY.NAME: Mary's Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Plain Or Peanut
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, 4 wide turn, best of rest

ENTRY.NAME: Modazzle
ENTRY.OWNER: Basler Thomas J and Pohl Dennis
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent inside, best

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Shaftesbury
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path turn, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: I'm Your Valentine
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3 wide turn, not enough late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Special Weight Purse 22000. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAST CROSS TRAFFIC briefly in tight quarters while rated on the front end from inside, did not stay with RUN THE TABLE after two furlongs, was roused just off the inside on the bend, all out deep stretch and got up in time. RUN THE TABLE shared the early lead just outside FAST CROSS TRAFFIC, moved clear after a quarter mile, put to urging upper stretch, did not have enough left in the waning yards but was easily second best. ITS MAMBO hesitated then bore in at the break, chased the top pair while well off the inside, came into the lane from path three and could only just hold onto third late. TEMPLE FOOL was away slowly, void of speed though urged along, just off the rail taking the bend, angled outside ITS MAMBO inside the final furlong and showed a willingness to run deep stretch. GRAYHOP was away very slowly, showed little, though urged along and distanced himself from the rest in the lane and was walked off after crossing the wire.

ENTRY.NAME: Its Mambo
ENTRY.COMMENT: hesitated, bore in start, 3-path turn, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Temple Fool
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, 2-3 path turn, angled out inside 1/8, late run

ENTRY.NAME: Fast Cross Traffic
ENTRY.OWNER: The Estate of Kenneth H Hutchens
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside, roused 2 wide turn, all out late, got up in time

ENTRY.NAME: Run the Table
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside speed, saved ground, not enough left

ENTRY.NAME: Grayhop
ENTRY.OWNER: The Estate of Kenneth H Hutchens
ENTRY.COMMENT: away slowly, no response, distanced, walked off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 79. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Si nce April 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO COOKIE RULE settled toward the outside, gradually closed the gap on the backstretch, gradually angled in as he circled rivals on the second bend, moved clear into the lane, lengthened command under urging upper stretch and maintained control while kept to task until near the wire. LONESOME DREAM exchanged bumps with AWESOME WILLY at the start, was prominent just off the inside, steadied in tight quarters between rivals into the second turn, fanned out widest for the stretch run, gradually drifted out as he rallied and got up for second in the final strides. ORBITAL STARR unhurried along the rail, picked up his pace after a half mile, swung around GHREAT PLAINES at the quarter pole, surged from inside in the lane and caught AWESOME WILLY for third near the wire. AWESOME WILLY exchanged bumps with LONESOME DREAM at the break, quickly recovered to vie for the early lead from inside, was no match for TWO COOKIE RULE after six furlongs, came off the rail some upper stretch, lacked the needed late kick and was outfinished from both sides in the waning yards. GREAT PLAINES displayed early speed from outside, began to fade three wide before finishing five furlongs, distanced himself in the stretch and was walked off after crossing the wire.

ENTRY.NAME: Orbital Starr
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside, 2 wide 1/4, surged inside stretch, got 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Two Cookie Rule
ENTRY.OWNER: Martin Paul E and Dellbringge Ronald
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated outside,roused after 1/2,circled foes 2nd turn,kept to task

ENTRY.NAME: Lonesome Dream
ENTRY.OWNER: Bugnitz John Elsner Brad and Rule Joe
ENTRY.COMMENT: in tight 7/16, steadied, 2-3 wide 2nd turn, drifted out stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Willy
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, angled 2 wide upper stretch, not enough left

ENTRY.NAME: Great Plaines
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-path speed, thru early, distanced stretch, walked off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD NON-WINNERS OF TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR IBF OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. No n-winners Of A Race Since April 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRIPLE SCOUT gradually angled in as she vied for the lead outside rivals from the early going, was three wide on the bend, came two wide into the stretch and shook off LONG TALL WOMAN nearing the final sixteenth. LONG TALL WOMAN bumped with DOROTA leaving the chute, soon disputed the pace between horses, bumped MISS WINDY SLEW nearing the half mile pole, vied in tight quarters from that point until just past the quarter pole, gained the rail into the lane and gradually wore down inside the last eighth. I LUV THIS BAR vied for the lead between rivals from the start, was caught in tight quarters just inside LONG TALL WOMAN into the bend, gained the rail soon after, began to retreat nearing the end of a half mile, swung out to path four leaving the turn and could only stay clear for third late. DOROTA bumped with LONG TALL WOMAN leaving the chute, was taken outside, advanced four wide on the turn, lost further ground floating out to path six entering the lane and had no late bid. BETHY was hustled along to contest the pace from inside on the backstretch but began to yield with three furlongs to go. MISS WINDY SLEW displayed early speed between rivals, was bumped and shuffled back nearing the end of two furlongs and steadily gave way. The rider of LONG TALL WOMAN lodged an objection alleging repeated interference from TRIPLE SCOUT. After their review, the stewards did not uphold that claim of foul.

ENTRY.NAME: Bethy
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent inside, thru early

ENTRY.NAME: I Luv This Bar
ENTRY.COMMENT: in tight between 7/16s,inside turn,angled out into stretch,evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Windy Slew
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, shuffled back 1/2, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Dorota
ENTRY.COMMENT: lost ground, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Long Tall Woman
ENTRY.COMMENT: in tight between early, in tight between 1/4,weakened inside late

ENTRY.NAME: Triple Scout
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 3 wide 1/4, 2 wide stretch, drew clear last 1/16
